\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
A Sufficient Introduction to R
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Derek Sonderegger
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This set of notes has grown out of teaching applied statistics courses at
 NAU to graduate students in Biology, Ecology and Forestry.
 Typically these students do not have a background in programming the scripting
 aspect of R is very challenging.
 I attempt to be clear and emphasize the major ideas but leave the documentation
 of the fine details to references that actually cost money or can be found
 on coding forums such as 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "Stack Exchange"
target "stackexchange.com"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While there is a definite statistical flair to the chosen examples, the
 reader is not assumed to have much statistical knowledge, and thus this
 tutorial can be read prior to an introductory statistical methods course,
 or more likely, concurrently with such a course.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Finally, I wish to thank the R community that has created such a wonderful
 resource and the package developers that have enriched it so greatly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Right Address
Derek Sonderegger
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Department of Mathematics and Statistics
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Northern Arizona University
\end_layout

